Global investors bought a net 9.09
billion rupees ($203.7 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 0.6 percent to 964 billion rupees, or 35.8
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 250 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on yesterday, according to preliminary data
